column9: From a primary thero (to heat); properly, heat, i.e. Summer -- summer.
From  (G2332) Thessalonike; a Thessalonican, i.e. Inhabitant of Thessalonice -- Thessalonian. see GREEK  (G2332) Thessalonike
From Thessalos (a Thessalian) and  (G3529) nike; Thessalonice, a place in Asia Minor -- Thessalonica. see GREEK  (G3529) nike
Of uncertain origin; Theudas, an Israelite -- Theudas.

From a derivative of  (G2300) theaomai (perhaps by addition of  (G3708) horao); to be a spectator of, i.e. Discern, (literally, figuratively (experience) or intensively (acknowledge)) -- behold, consider, look on, perceive, see. Compare  (G3700) optanomai. see GREEK  (G2300) theaomai see GREEK  (G3708) horao see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
From the same as  (G2334) theoreo; spectatorship, i.e. (concretely) a spectacle -- sight. see GREEK  (G2334) theoreo
From  (G5087) tithemi; a receptacle, i.e. Scabbard -- sheath. see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
From thele (the nipple); to suckle, (by implication) to suck -- (give) suck(-ling).
From the same as  (G2337) thelazo; female -- female, woman. see GREEK  (G2337) thelazo
From ther (a wild animal, as game); hunting, i.e. (figuratively) destruction -- trap.
From  (G2339) thera; to hunt (an animal), i.e. (figuratively) to carp at -- catch. see GREEK  (G2339) thera

From a compound of  (G2342) therion and  (G3164) machomai; to be a beast-fighter (in the gladiatorial show), i.e. (figuratively) to encounter (furious men) -- fight with wild beasts. see GREEK  (G2342) therion see GREEK  (G3164) machomai
Diminutive from the same as  (G2339) thera; a dangerous animal -- (venomous, wild) beast. see GREEK  (G2339) thera

column8: lay up treasure, keep in store.
column9: From  (G2344) thesauros; to amass or reserve (literally or figuratively) -- lay up (treasure), (keep) in store, (heap) treasure (together, up). see GREEK  (G2344) thesauros
From  (G5087) tithemi; a deposit, i.e. Wealth (literally or figuratively) -- treasure. see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
A prolonged form of an obsolete primary thigo (to finger); to manipulate, i.e. Have to do with; by implication, to injure -- handle, touch.
Akin to the base of  (G5147) tribos; to crowd (literally or figuratively) -- afflict, narrow, throng, suffer tribulation, trouble. see GREEK  (G5147) tribos
From  (G2346) thlibo; pressure (literally or figuratively) -- afflicted(-tion), anguish, burdened, persecution, tribulation, trouble. see GREEK  (G2346) thlibo
A strengthened form of a simpler primary thano than'-o (which is used for it only in certain tenses); to die (literally or figuratively) -- be dead, die.
From  (G2348) thnesko; liable to die -- mortal(-ity). see GREEK  (G2348) thnesko
From  (G2351) thorubos; to be in tumult, i.e. Disturb, clamor -- make ado (a noise), trouble self, set on an uproar. see GREEK  (G2351) thorubos
From the base of  (G2360) throeo; a disturbance -- tumult, uproar. see GREEK  (G2360) throeo
A primary verb; to crush -- bruise. Compare  (G4486) rhegnumi. see GREEK  (G4486) rhegnumi
From  (G5142) trepho; stock (as raised on a farm) -- cattle. see GREEK  (G5142) trepho
From  (G2355) threnos; to bewail -- lament, mourn. see GREEK  (G2355) threnos
From the base of  (G2360) throeo; wailing -- lamentation. see GREEK  (G2360) throeo
From a derivative of  (G2357) threskos; ceremonial observance -- religion, worshipping. see GREEK  (G2357) threskos
Probably from the base of  (G2360) throeo; ceremonious in worship (as demonstrative), i.e. Pious -- religious. see GREEK  (G2360) throeo

From a prolonged compound of the base of  (G2360) throeo; and a derivative of  (G680) haptomai (meaning a noisy iambus, sung in honor of Bacchus); to make an acclamatory procession, i.e. (figuratively) to conquer or (by Hebraism) to give victory -- (cause) to triumph (over). see GREEK  (G2360) throeo see GREEK  (G680) haptomai
Genitive case trichos, etc.; of uncertain derivation; hair -- hair. Compare  (G2864) kome. see GREEK  (G2864) kome
From threomai to wail; to clamor, i.e. (by implication) to frighten -- trouble.
Perhaps from  (G5142) trepho (in the sense of thickening); a clot -- great drop. see GREEK  (G5142) trepho
From thrao (to sit); a stately seat ("throne"); by implication, power or (concretely) a potentate -- seat, throne.
Of uncertain derivation; Thyatira, a place in Asia Minor -- Thyatira.
Apparently a primary word (compare "daughter"); a female child, or (by Hebraism) descendant (or inhabitant) -- daughter.
From  (G2364) thugater; a daughterling -- little (young) daughter. see GREEK  (G2364) thugater
From  (G2380) thuo (in the sense of blowing) a storm -- tempest. see GREEK  (G2380) thuo
From a derivative of  (G2380) thuo (in the sense of blowing; denoting a certain fragrant tree); made of citron-wood -- thyine. see GREEK  (G2380) thuo
From  (G2370) thumiao; an aroma, i.e. Fragrant powder burnt in religious service; by implication, the burning itself -- incense, odour. see GREEK  (G2370) thumiao

column8: an altar of incense, a censer
column9: From a derivative of  (G2370) thumiao; a place of fumigation, i.e. The alter of incense (in the Temple) -- censer. see GREEK  (G2370) thumiao
From a derivative of  (G2380) thuo (in the sense of smoking); to fumigate, i.e. Offer aromatic fumes -- burn incense. see GREEK  (G2380) thuo

From a presumed compound of  (G2372) thumos and  (G3164) machomai; to be in a furious fight, i.e. (figuratively) to be exasperated -- be highly displeased. see GREEK  (G2372) thumos see GREEK  (G3164) machomai
From  (G2380) thuo; passion (as if breathing hard) -- fierceness, indignation, wrath. Compare  (G5590) psuche. see GREEK  (G2380) thuo see GREEK  (G5590) psuche
From  (G2372) thumos; to put in a passion, i.e. Enrage -- be wroth. see GREEK  (G2372) thumos
Apparently a primary word (compare "door"); a portal or entrance (the opening or the closure, literally or figuratively) -- door, gate.
From  (G2374) thura; a large shield (as door-shaped) -- shield. see GREEK  (G2374) thura
From  (G2374) thura; an aperture, i.e. Window -- window. see GREEK  (G2374) thura
From  (G2374) thura and ouros (a watcher); a gate- warden -- that kept the door, porter. see GREEK  (G2374) thura
From  (G2380) thuo; sacrifice (the act or the victim, literally or figuratively) -- sacrifice. see GREEK  (G2380) thuo
From a derivative of  (G2378) thusia; a place of sacrifice, i.e. An altar (special or genitive case, literal or figurative) -- altar. see GREEK  (G2378) thusia

A primary verb; properly, to rush (breathe hard, blow, smoke), i.e. (by implication) to sacrifice (properly, by fire, but genitive case); by extension to immolate (slaughter for any purpose) -- kill, (do) sacrifice, slay.

column7: the twin, Thomas, one of the twelve apostles
column9: Of Chaldee origin (compare  (H8380) ta'owm); the twin; Thomas, a Christian -- Thomas. see HEBREW  (H8380) ta'owm
Of uncertain affinity; the chest ("thorax"), i.e. (by implication) a corslet -- breast-plate.

column7: Jairus, the ruler of a synagogue in Palestine
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H2971) Ya'iyr); Jairus (i.e. Jair), an Israelite -- Jairus. see HEBREW  (H2971) Ya'iyr

column7: Jacob, the son of Isaac, also the father of Joseph, Mary\'s husband
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H3290) Ya'aqob); Jacob (i.e. Ja'akob), the progenitor of the Israelites -- also an Israelite -- Jacob. see HEBREW  (H3290) Ya'aqob

column7: James, the name of several Israelites
column9: The same as  (G2384) Iakob Graecized; Jacobus, the name of three Israelites -- James. see GREEK  (G2384) Iakob
From  (G2390) iaomai; a cure (the effect) -- healing. see GREEK  (G2390) iaomai
Of Egyptian origin; Jambres, an Egyptian -- Jambres.
Probably of Hebrew origin (compare  (H3238) yanah); Janna, an Israelite -- Janna. see HEBREW  (H3238) yanah
Of Egyptian origin; Jannes, an Egyptian -- Jannes.
Middle voice of apparently a primary verb; to cure (literally or figuratively) -- heal, make whole.
Of Hebrew origin ( (H3382) Yered); Jared (i.e. Jered), an antediluvian -- Jared. see HEBREW  (H3382) Yered
From  (G2390) iaomai; curing (the act) -- cure, heal(-ing). see GREEK  (G2390) iaomai
Probably of foreign origin (see  (H3471) yashpheh); "jasper", a gem -- jasper. see HEBREW  (H3471) yashpheh

column7: Jason, the name of one, perhaps two, Christian

From  (G2390) iaomai; a physician -- physician. see GREEK  (G2390) iaomai
Second person singular imperative active of  (G1492) eido; used as an interjection to denote surprise; lo! -- behold, lo, see. see GREEK  (G1492) eido
From  (G1492) eido; a sight (comparative figuratively "idea"), i.e. Aspect -- countenance. see GREEK  (G1492) eido

Of uncertain affinity; pertaining to self, i.e. One's own; by implication, private or separate -- X his acquaintance, when they were alone, apart, aside, due, his (own, proper, several), home, (her, our, thine, your) own (business), private(-ly), proper, severally, their (own).
From  (G2398) idios; a private person, i.e. (by implication) an ignoramus (compare "idiot") -- ignorant, rude, unlearned. see GREEK  (G2398) idios
Second person singular imperative middle voice of  (G1492) eido; used as imperative lo!; --behold, lo, see. see GREEK  (G1492) eido

column7: Idumea, a region South of Judea
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H123) 'Edom); Idumaea (i.e. Edom), a region East (and South) of Palestine -- Idumaea. see HEBREW  (H123) 'Edom
A strengthened form of a primary idos (sweat): perspiration -- sweat.

column7: Jezebel, the symbolic name of a false prophetess
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H348) 'Iyzebel); Jezabel (i.e. Jezebel), a Tyrian woman (used as a synonym of a termagant or false teacher) -- Jezabel. see HEBREW  (H348) 'Iyzebel
From  (G2413) hieros and  (G4172) polis; holy city; Hierapolis, a place in Asia Minor -- Hierapolis. see GREEK  (G2413) hieros see GREEK  (G4172) polis

column8: office of the priesthood, priest's office.

From  (G2407) hierateuo; the priestly fraternity, i.e. Sacerdotal order (figuratively) -- priesthood. see GREEK  (G2407) hierateuo
Prolongation from  (G2409) hiereus; to be a priest, i.e. Perform his functions -- execute the priest's office. see GREEK  (G2409) hiereus
Of Hebrew origin ( (H3414) Yirmyah); Hieremias (i.e. Jermijah), an Israelite -- Jeremiah. see HEBREW  (H3414) Yirmyah
From  (G2413) hieros; a priest (literally or figuratively) -- (high) priest. see GREEK  (G2413) hieros
Of Hebrew origin ( (H3405) Yriychow); Jericho, a place in Palestine -- Jericho. see HEBREW  (H3405) Yriychow

Neuter of  (G2413) hieros; a sacred place, i.e. The entire precincts (whereas  (G3485) naos denotes the central sanctuary itself) of the Temple (at Jerusalem or elsewhere) -- temple. see GREEK  (G2413) hieros see GREEK  (G3485) naos
From  (G2413) hieros and the same as  (G4241) prepo; reverent -- as becometh holiness. see GREEK  (G2413) hieros see GREEK  (G4241) prepo

column7: sacred, a sacred thing, a temple
column9: Of uncertain affinity; sacred -- holy.

column7: Jerusalem, the capital of united Israel and Judah

From  (G2414) Hierosoluma; a Hierosolymite, i.e. Inhabitant of Hierosolyma -- of Jerusalem. see GREEK  (G2414) Hierosoluma

column7: Jerusalem, the capital of united Israel and Judah, also a future heavenly city

From  (G2413) hieros; sacredness, i.e. (by implication) the priestly office -- priesthood. see GREEK  (G2413) hieros

column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H3448) Yishay); Jessae (i.e. Jishai), an Israelite -- Jesse. see HEBREW  (H3448) Yishay

Of Hebrew origin ( (H3204) Ykonyah); Jechonias (i.e. Jekonjah), an Israelite -- Jechonias. see HEBREW  (H3204) Ykonyah

column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H3091) Yhowshuwa'); Jesus (i.e. Jehoshua), the name of our Lord and two (three) other Israelites -- Jesus. see HEBREW  (H3091) Yhowshuwa'

From  (G2425) hikanos; ability -- sufficiency. see GREEK  (G2425) hikanos
From  (G2425) hikanos; to enable, i.e. Qualify -- make able (meet). see GREEK  (G2425) hikanos
From a derivative of the base of  (G2425) hikanos (through the idea of approaching for a favor); intreaty -- supplication. see GREEK  (G2425) hikanos
Of uncertain affinity; dampness -- moisture.
Perhaps from  (G1504) eikon; image-like; Iconium, a place in Asia Minor -- Iconium. see GREEK  (G1504) eikon
From the same as  (G2436) hileos; propitious or merry ("hilarious"), i.e. Prompt or willing -- cheerful. see GREEK  (G2436) hileos
From  (G2431) hilaros; alacrity -- cheerfulness. see GREEK  (G2431) hilaros

column9: Neuter of an adjective from a name of uncertain derivation: (the) Illyrican (shore), i.e. (as a name itself) Illyricum, a region of Europe -- Illyricum.
Perhaps from the same as  (G260) hama; a strap, i.e. (specially) the tie (of a sandal) or the lash (of a scourge) -- latchet, thong. see GREEK  (G260) hama
From  (G2440) himation; to dress -- clothe. see GREEK  (G2440) himation

column9: Neuter of a presumed derivative of ennumi (to put on); a dress (inner or outer) -- apparel, cloke, clothes, garment, raiment, robe, vesture.
From  (G2439) himatizo; clothing -- apparel (X -led), array, raiment, vesture. see GREEK  (G2439) himatizo
Middle voice from himeros (a yearning; of uncertain affinity); to long for -- be affectionately desirous.

column7: in order that, that, so that
column8: albeit, because, in order that, lest
column9: Probably from the same as the former part of  (G1438) heautou (through the demonstrative idea; compare  (G3588) ho); in order that (denoting the purpose or the result) -- albeit, because, to the intent (that), lest, so as, (so) that, (for) to. From  (G2443) hina and  (G5101) tis; for what reason ?, i.e. Why? -- wherefore, why. see GREEK  (G2443) hina see GREEK  (G5101) tis
Of Hebrew origin ( (H3305) Yapho); Joppe (i.e. Japho), a place in Palestine -- Joppa. see HEBREW  (H3305) Yapho

column7: the Jordan, the largest river of Pal
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H3383) Yarden); the Jordanes (i.e. Jarden), a river of Palestine -- Jordan. see HEBREW  (H3383) Yarden
Perhaps from eimi (to go) or hiemi (to send); rust (as if emitted by metals); also venom (as emitted by serpents) -- poison, rust.
Of Hebrew origin ( (H3063) Yhuwdah or perhaps  (H3194) Yuttah); Judah (i.e. Jehudah or Juttah), a part of (or place in) Palestine -- Judah. see HEBREW  (H3063) Yhuwdah see HEBREW  (H3194) Yuttah
Feminine of  (G2453) Ioudaios (with  (G1093) ge implied); the Judaean land (i.e. Judaea), a region of Palestine -- Judaea. see GREEK  (G2453) Ioudaios see GREEK  (G1093) ge
From  (G2453) Ioudaios; to become a Judaean, i.e. "Judaize" -- live as the Jews. see GREEK  (G2453) Ioudaios
From  (G2453) Ioudaios; Judaic, i.e. Resembling a Judaean -- Jewish. see GREEK  (G2453) Ioudaios
Adverb from  (G2451) Ioudaikos; Judaically or in a manner resembling a Judaean -- as do the Jews. see GREEK  (G2451) Ioudaikos
From  (G2448) Iouda (in the sense of  (G2455) Ioudas as a country); Judaean, i.e. Belonging to Jehudah -- Jew(-ess), of Judaea. see GREEK  (G2448) Iouda see GREEK  (G2455) Ioudas
From  (G2450) Ioudaizo; "Judaism", i.e. The Jewish faith and usages -- Jews' religion. see GREEK  (G2450) Ioudaizo

column7: Judah, Judas, the name of several Israelites, also one of the twelve tribes of Isr., also the Southern kingdom
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H3063) Yhuwdah); Judas (i.e. Jehudah), the name of ten Israelites; also of the posterity of one of them and its region -- Juda(-h, -s); Jude. see HEBREW  (H3063) Yhuwdah
Feminine of the same as  (G2457) Ioulios; Julia, a Christian woman -- Julia. see GREEK  (G2457) Ioulios
Of Latin origin; Julius, a centurion -- Julius.
Of Latin origin; Junias, a Christian -- Junias.

column7: Justus, the name of three Christians
column9: Of Latin origin ("just"); Justus, the name of three Christian -- Justus.
From  (G2462) hippos; an equestrian, i.e. Member of a cavalry corps -- horseman. see GREEK  (G2462) hippos
Neuter of a derivative of  (G2462) hippos; the cavalry force -- horse(-men). see GREEK  (G2462) hippos
Of uncertain affinity; a horse -- horse.
Perhaps from  (G2046) ereo (as a symbol of the female messenger of the pagan deities); a rainbow ("iris") -- rainbow. see GREEK  (G2046) ereo
Of Hebrew origin ( (H3327) Yitschaq); Isaac (i.e. Jitschak), the son of Abraham -- Isaac. see HEBREW  (H3327) Yitschaq
From  (G2470) isos and  (G32) aggelos; like an angel, i.e. Angelic -- equal unto the angels. see GREEK  (G2470) isos see GREEK  (G32) aggelos
Of Hebrew origin ( (H3485) Yissaskar); Isachar (i.e. Jissaskar), a son of Jacob (figuratively, his descendant) -- Issachar. see HEBREW  (H3485) Yissaskar
Assumed by some as the base of certain irregular forms of  (G1942) epikaluma; to know -- know. see GREEK  (G1942) epikaluma
Second person imperative present of  (G1510) eimi; be thou -- + agree, be, X give thyself wholly to. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi

column7: Iscariot, surname of Judas and his father
column9: Of Hebrew origin (probably  (H377) 'iysh and  (H7149) qirya'); inhabitant of Kerioth; Iscariotes (i.e. Keriothite), an epithet of Judas the traitor -- Iscariot. see HEBREW  (H377) 'iysh see HEBREW  (H7149) qirya'
Probably from  (G1492) eido (through the idea of seeming); similar (in amount and kind) -- + agree, as much, equal, like. see GREEK  (G1492) eido
Likeness (in condition or proportion); by implication, equity -- equal(-ity).

column8: equal, like, of the same kind
column9: From  (G2470) isos and  (G5092) time; of equal value or honor -- like precious. see GREEK  (G2470) isos see GREEK  (G5092) time
From  (G2470) isos and  (G5590) psuche; of similar spirit -- likeminded. see GREEK  (G2470) isos see GREEK  (G5590) psuche

column7: Israel, the name of the Jewish people and their land
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H3478) Yisra'el); Israel (i.e. Jisrael), the adopted name of Jacob, including his descendants (literally or figuratively) -- Israel. see HEBREW  (H3478) Yisra'el
From  (G2474) Israel; an "Israelite", i.e. Descendant of Israel (literally or figuratively) -- Israelite. see GREEK  (G2474) Israel

column7: to make to stand, to stand
column8: cause to stand, establish, hold up
column9: A prolonged form of a primary stao stah'-o (of the same meaning, and used for it in certain tenses); to stand (transitively or intransitively), used in various applications (literally or figuratively) -- abide, appoint, bring, continue, covenant, establish, hold up, lay, present, set (up), stanch, stand (by, forth, still, up). From a derivative of  (G1492) eido; to be knowing (learned), i.e. (by implication) to visit for information (interview) -- see. see GREEK  (G1492) eido
From  (G2479) ischus; forcible (literally or figuratively) -- boisterous, mighty(-ier), powerful, strong(-er, man), valiant. see GREEK  (G2479) ischus
From a derivative of is (force; compare eschon, a form of  (G2192) echo); forcefulness (literally or figuratively) -- ability, might(-ily), power, strength. see GREEK  (G2192) echo

column8: be able, prevail, be of strength
column9: From  (G2479) ischus; to have (or exercise) force (literally or figuratively) -- be able, avail, can do(-not), could, be good, might, prevail, be of strength, be whole, + much work. see GREEK  (G2479) ischus
Adverb from  (G2470) isos; likely, i.e. Perhaps -- it may be. see GREEK  (G2470) isos

column7: Italy, a region of western Europe
column9: Probably of foreign origin; Italia, a region of Europe -- Italy.
From  (G2482) Italia; Italic, i.e. Belonging to Italia -- Italian. see GREEK  (G2482) Italia

column7: Ituraea, a region North of Pal
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H3195) Ytuwr); Ituraea (i.e. Jetur), a region of Palestine -- Ituraea. see HEBREW  (H3195) Ytuwr
Diminutive from  (G2486) ichthus; a petty fish -- little (small) fish. see GREEK  (G2486) ichthus
Of uncertain affinity; a fish -- fish.
From ikneomai (to arrive; compare  (G2240) heko); a track (figuratively) -- step. see GREEK  (G2240) heko
Of Hebrew origin ( (H3147) Yowtham); Joatham (i.e. Jotham), an Israelite -- Joatham. see HEBREW  (H3147) Yowtham
Feminine of the same as  (G2491) Ioannes; Joanna, a Christian -- Joanna. see GREEK  (G2491) Ioannes
A form of  (G2491) Ioannes; Joannas, an Israelite -- Joannas. see GREEK  (G2491) Ioannes

column7: John, the name of several Israelites

From  (G2513) katharos; to cleanse, i.e. (specially) to prune; figuratively, to expiate -- purge. see GREEK  (G2513) katharos

From  (G2513) katharos; to cleanse (literally or figuratively) -- (make) clean(-se), purge, purify. see GREEK  (G2513) katharos

From  (G2513) katharos; cleanness (ceremonially) -- purification. see GREEK  (G2513) katharos

From a compound of  (G2596) kata and  (G2233) hegeomai; a guide, i.e. (figuratively) a teacher -- master. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2233) hegeomai
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2240) heko; to reach to, i.e. (neuter of present active participle, figuratively as adjective) becoming -- convenient, fit. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2240) heko

From  (G2596) kata; and hemai (to sit; akin to the base of  (G1476) hedraios); to sit down; figuratively, to remain, reside -- dwell, sit (by, down). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1476) hedraios
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2250) hemera; quotidian -- daily. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2250) hemera

column7: to make to sit down, to sit down

From  (G2596) kata; and hiemi (to send); to lower -- let down. see GREEK  (G2596) kata

From  (G2596) kata; and  (G3695) hoplizo; to equip fully with armor -- arm. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3695) hoplizo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G3708) horao; to behold fully, i.e. (figuratively) distinctly apprehend -- clearly see. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3708) horao

From  (G2596) kata and  (G5613) hos; just (or inasmuch) as, that -- according to, (according, even) as, how, when. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5613) hos

column8: and, also, both, but, even, for, if, or, so
column9: Apparently, a primary particle, having a copulative and sometimes also a cumulative force; and, also, even, so then, too, etc.; often used in connection (or composition) with other particles or small words -- and, also, both, but, even, for, if, or, so, that, then, therefore, when, yet.

From  (G2532) kai and  (G4007) per; and indeed, i.e. Nevertheless or notwithstanding -- and yet, although. see GREEK  (G2532) kai see GREEK  (G4007) per

From  (G2543) kaitoi and  (G1065) ge; and yet indeed, i.e. Although really -- nevertheless, though. see GREEK  (G2543) kaitoi see GREEK  (G1065) ge

From a compound of  (G2556) kakos and  (G3056) logos; to revile -- curse, speak evil of. see GREEK  (G2556) kakos see GREEK  (G3056) logos

From  (G2556) kakos and  (G4160) poieo; a bad-doer; (specially), a criminal -- evil-doer, malefactor. see GREEK  (G2556) kakos see GREEK  (G4160) poieo

Apparently a primary word; worthless (intrinsically, such; whereas  (G4190) poneros properly refers to effects), i.e. (subjectively) depraved, or (objectively) injurious -- bad, evil, harm, ill, noisome, wicked. see GREEK  (G4190) poneros
From  (G2556) kakos and the base of  (G2041) ergon; a wrong-doer, i.e. Criminal -- evil-doer, malefactor. see GREEK  (G2556) kakos see GREEK  (G2041) ergon
From a presumed compound of  (G2556) kakos and  (G2192) echo; to maltreat -- which suffer adversity, torment. see GREEK  (G2556) kakos see GREEK  (G2192) echo
From  (G2556) kakos; to injure; figuratively, to exasperate -- make evil affected, entreat evil, harm, hurt, vex. see GREEK  (G2556) kakos
From  (G2556) kakos; badly (physically or morally) -- amiss, diseased, evil, grievously, miserably, sick, sore. see GREEK  (G2556) kakos
From  (G2559) kakoo; maltreatment -- affliction. see GREEK  (G2559) kakoo

Akin to the base of  (G2753) keleuo; to "call" (properly, aloud, but used in a variety of applications, directly or otherwise) -- bid, call (forth), (whose, whose sur-)name (was (called)). see GREEK  (G2753) keleuo

From  (G2570) kalos and  (G4160) poieo; to do well, i.e. Live virtuously -- well doing. see GREEK  (G2570) kalos see GREEK  (G4160) poieo

From  (G2572) kalupto; a cover, i.e. Veil -- vail. see GREEK  (G2572) kalupto

From a compound of  (G2596) kata and the base of  (G3466) musterion; to shut down, i.e. Close the eyes -- close. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3466) musterion

Apparently a primary verb; to bend -- bow.

Of foreign origin -- Candace, an Egyptian queen -- Candace.
From kane (a straight reed, i.e. Rod); a rule ("canon"), i.e. (figuratively) a standard (of faith and practice); by implication, a boundary, i.e. (figuratively) a sphere (of activity) -- line, rule.

From kapelos (a huckster); to retail, i.e. (by implication) to adulterate (figuratively) -- corrupt.
Of uncertain affinity; smoke -- smoke.

column7: Cappadocia, a province of Asia Minor
column9: Of foreign origin; Cappadocia, a region of Asia Minor -- Cappadocia.
Prolonged from a primary kar (Latin cor, "heart"); the heart, i.e. (figuratively) the thoughts or feelings (mind); also (by analogy) the middle -- (+ broken-)heart(-ed).
From  (G2588) kardia and  (G1097) ginosko; a heart-knower -- which knowest the hearts. see GREEK  (G2588) kardia see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko

Perhaps for  (G2590) karpos; Carpus, probably a Christian -- Carpus. see GREEK  (G2590) karpos
From  (G2593) karpophoros; to be fertile (literally or figuratively) -- be (bear, bring forth) fruit(-ful). see GREEK  (G2593) karpophoros
From  (G2590) karpos and  (G5342) phero; fruitbearing (figuratively) -- fruitful. see GREEK  (G2590) karpos see GREEK  (G5342) phero
From a derivative of  (G2904) kratos (transposed); to be strong, i.e. (figuratively) steadfast (patient) -- endure. see GREEK  (G2904) kratos
From karpho (to wither); a dry twig or straw -- mote.

A primary particle; (prepositionally) down (in place or time), in varied relations (according to the case (genitive, dative or accusative) with which it is joined) -- about, according as (to), after, against, (when they were) X alone, among, and, X apart, (even, like) as (concerning, pertaining to touching), X aside, at, before, beyond, by, to the charge of, (charita-)bly, concerning, + covered, (dai-)ly, down, every, (+ far more) exceeding, X more excellent, for, from... To, godly, in(-asmuch, divers, every, -to, respect of),... By, after the manner of, + by any means, beyond (out of) measure, X mightily, more, X natural, of (up-)on (X part), out (of every), over against, (+ your) X own, + particularly, so, through(-oughout, -oughout every), thus, (un-)to(-gether, -ward), X uttermost, where(-by), with. In composition it retains many of these applications, and frequently denotes opposition, distribution, or intensity.
From  (G2596) kata and the base of  (G939) basis; to descend (literally or figuratively) -- come (get, go, step) down, fall (down). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G939) basis
From  (G2596) kata and  (G906) ballo; to throw down -- cast down, lay. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G906) ballo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G916) bareo; to impose upon -- burden. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G916) bareo
From  (G2597) katabaino; a declivity -- descent. see GREEK  (G2597) katabaino
From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of the base of  (G939) basis; to cause to go down, i.e. Precipitate -- bring (thrust) down. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G939) basis
From  (G2598) kataballo; a deposition, i.e. Founding; figuratively, conception -- conceive, foundation. see GREEK  (G2598) kataballo

From  (G2596) kata and  (G1018) brabeuo (in its original sense); to award the price against, i.e. (figuratively) to defraud (of salvation) -- beguile of reward. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1018) brabeuo
From  (G2605) kataggello; a proclaimer -- setter forth. see GREEK  (G2605) kataggello
From  (G2596) kata and the base of  (G32) aggelos; to proclaim, promulgate -- declare, preach, shew, speak of, teach. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G32) aggelos
To laugh down, i.e. Deride -- laugh to scorn.
From  (G2596) kata and  (G1097) ginosko; to note against, i.e. Find fault with -- blame, condemn. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko
From  (G2596) kata and the base of  (G4486) rhegnumi; to rend in pieces, i.e. Crack apart -- break. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4486) rhegnumi
From  (G2596) kata and  (G71) ago; to lead down; specially, to moor a vessel -- bring (down, forth), (bring to) land, touch. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G2596) kata and  (G75) agonizomai; to struggle against, i.e. (by implication) to overcome -- subdue. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G75) agonizomai
From  (G2596) kata and  (G1210) deo; to tie down, i.e. Bandage (a wound) -- bind up. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1210) deo
From  (G2596) kata intensive and  (G1212) delos; manifest -- far more evident. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1212) delos
From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G1349) dike; to adjudge against, i.e. Pronounce guilty -- condemn. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1349) dike
From  (G2596) kata and  (G1377) dioko; to hunt down, i.e. Search for -- follow after. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1377) dioko
From  (G2596) kata and  (G1402) douloo; to enslave utterly -- bring into bondage. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1402) douloo
From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G1413) dunastes; to exercise dominion against, i.e. Oppress -- oppress. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1413) dunastes

From  (G2596) kata and  (G153) aischunomai; to shame down, i.e. Disgrace or (by implication) put to the blush -- confound, dishonour, (be a-, make a-)shame(-d). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G153) aischunomai
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2545) kaio; to burn down (to the ground), i.e. Consume wholly -- burn (up, utterly). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2545) kaio
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2572) kalupto; to cover wholly, i.e. Veil -- cover, hide. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2572) kalupto
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2744) kauchaomai; to exult against (i.e. Over) -- boast (against), glory, rejoice against. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2744) kauchaomai

column8: recline, lie, sit down at meals
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G2749) keimai; to lie down, i.e. (by implication) be sick; specially, to recline at a meal -- keep, lie, sit at meat (down). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2749) keimai
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2806) klao; to break down, i.e. Divide -- break. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2806) klao
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2808) kleio; to shut down (in a dungeon), i.e. Incarcerate -- shut up. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2808) kleio

column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G2827) klino; to recline down, i.e. (specially) to take a place at table -- (make) sit down (at meat). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2827) klino
From  (G2596) kata and the base of  (G2830) kludon; to dash (wash) down, i.e. (by implication) to deluge -- overflow. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2830) kludon
From  (G2626) katakluzo; an inundation -- flood. see GREEK  (G2626) katakluzo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G190) akoloutheo; to accompany closely -- follow (after). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G190) akoloutheo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2875) kopto; to chop down, i.e. Mangle -- cut. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2875) kopto
From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G2911) kremnos; to precipitate down -- cast down headlong. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2911) kremnos
From  (G2632) katakrino; an adverse sentence (the verdict) -- condemnation. see GREEK  (G2632) katakrino
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2919) krino; to judge against, i.e. Sentence -- condemn, damn. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2919) krino
From  (G2632) katakrino; sentencing adversely (the act) -- condemn(-ation). see GREEK  (G2632) katakrino

column8: exercise dominion over, be lord over, overcome.
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G2961) kurieuo; to lord against, i.e. Control, subjugate -- exercise dominion over (lordship), be lord over, overcome. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2961) kurieuo
From  (G2637) katalalos; to be a traducer, i.e. To slander -- speak against (evil of). see GREEK  (G2637) katalalos
From  (G2637) katalalos; defamation -- backbiting, evil speaking. see GREEK  (G2637) katalalos
From  (G2596) kata and the base of  (G2980) laleo; talkative against, i.e. A slanderer -- backbiter. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2980) laleo

From  (G2596) kata and  (G2983) lambano; to take eagerly, i.e. Seize, possess, etc. (literally or figuratively) -- apprehend, attain, come upon, comprehend, find, obtain, perceive, (over-)take. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2983) lambano

column8: to enroll, place on a list
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G3004) lego (in its original meaning); to lay down, i.e. (figuratively) to enrol -- take into the number. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3004) lego
From  (G2641) kataleipo; a remainder, i.e. (by implication) a few -- remnant. see GREEK  (G2641) kataleipo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G3007) leipo; to leave down, i.e. Behind; by implication, to abandon, have remaining -- forsake, leave, reserve. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3007) leipo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G3034) lithazo; to stone down, i.e. To death -- stone. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3034) lithazo
From  (G2644) katallasso; exchange (figuratively, adjustment), i.e. Restoration to (the divine) favor -- atonement, reconciliation(-ing). see GREEK  (G2644) katallasso
From  (G2596) kata and  (G236) allasso; to change mutually, i.e. (figuratively) to compound a difference -- reconcile. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G236) allasso
From  (G2596) kata and  (G3062) loipoy; left down (behind), i.e remaining (plural the rest) -- residue. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3062) loipoy
From  (G2647) kataluo; properly, a dissolution (breaking up of a journey), i.e. (by implication) a lodging-place -- guestchamber, inn. see GREEK  (G2647) kataluo

column8: destroy, dissolve, lodge, come to nought
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G3089) luo; to loosen down (disintegrate), i.e. (by implication) to demolish (literally or figuratively); specially (compare  (G2646) kataluma) to halt for the night -- destroy, dissolve, be guest, lodge, come to nought, overthrow, throw down. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3089) luo see GREEK  (G2646) kataluma
From  (G2596) kata and  (G3129) manthano; to learn thoroughly, i.e. (by implication) to note carefully -- consider. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3129) manthano

column7: to testify or bear witness against
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G3140) martureo; to testify against -- witness against. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3140) martureo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G3306) meno; to stay fully, i.e. Reside -- abide. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3306) meno

From  (G2596) kata and accusative case plural feminine of  (G3441) monos (with  (G5561) chora implied); according to sole places, i.e. (adverbially) separately -- alone. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3441) monos see GREEK  (G5561) chora
From  (G2596) kata (intensive) and  (G331) anathema; an imprecation -- curse. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G331) anathema
From  (G2596) kata (intensive) and  (G332) anathematizo; to imprecate -- curse. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G332) anathematizo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G355) analisko; to consume utterly -- consume. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G355) analisko
From  (G2596) kata and narkao (to be numb); to grow utterly torpid, i.e. (by implication) slothful (figuratively, expensive) -- be burdensome (chargeable). see GREEK  (G2596) kata

column7: to make a sign (by nodding the head)
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G3506) neuo; to nod down (towards), i.e. (by analogy) to make signs to -- beckon. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3506) neuo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G3539) noieo; to observe fully -- behold, consider, discover, perceive. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3539) noieo
From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G473) anti; to meet against, i.e. Arrive at (literally or figuratively) -- attain, come. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G473) anti

From  (G2660) katanusso; a prickling (sensation, as of the limbs asleep), i.e. (by implication, (perhaps by some confusion with  (G3506) neuo or even with  (G3571) nux)) stupor (lethargy) -- slumber. see GREEK  (G2660) katanusso see GREEK  (G3506) neuo see GREEK  (G3571) nux
From  (G2596) kata and  (G3572) nusso; to pierce thoroughly, i.e. (figuratively) to agitate violently ("sting to the quick") -- prick. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3572) nusso
From  (G2596) kata and  (G515) axioo; to deem entirely deserving -- (ac-)count worthy. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G515) axioo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G3961) pateo; to trample down; figuratively, to reject with disdain -- trample, tread (down, underfoot). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3961) pateo
From  (G2664) katapauo; reposing down, i.e. (by Hebraism) abode -- rest. see GREEK  (G2664) katapauo

column7: to cause to cease, to rest
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G3973) pauo; to settle down, i.e. (literally) to colonize, or (figuratively) to (cause to) desist -- cease, (give) rest(-rain). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3973) pauo

column7: a curtain (the inner veil of the temple)
column9: From a compound of  (G2596) kata and a congener of  (G4072) petomai; something spread thoroughly, i.e. (specially) the door screen (to the Most Holy Place) in the Jewish Temple -- vail. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4072) petomai
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4095) pino; to drink down, i.e. Gulp entire (literally or figuratively) -- devour, drown, swallow (up). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4095) pino
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4098) pipto; to fall down -- fall (down) see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4098) pipto
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4126) pleo; to sail down upon a place, i.e. To land at -- arrive. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4126) pleo
From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G4192) ponos; to labor down, i.e. Wear with toil (figuratively, harass) -- oppress, vex. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4192) ponos
From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of the same as  (G4195) Pontos; to plunge down, i.e. Submerge -- drown, sink. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4195) Pontos
From  (G2596) kata (intensive) and  (G685) ara; imprecation, execration -- curse(-d, ing). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G685) ara
Middle voice from  (G2671) katara; to execrate; by analogy, to doom -- curse. see GREEK  (G2671) katara

From  (G2596) kata and  (G691) argeo; to be (render) entirely idle (useless), literally or figuratively -- abolish, cease, cumber, deliver, destroy, do away, become (make) of no (none, without) effect, fail, loose, bring (come) to nought, put away (down), vanish away, make void. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G691) argeo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G705) arithmeo; to reckon among -- number with. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G705) arithmeo

From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G739) artios; to complete thoroughly, i.e. Repair (literally or figuratively) or adjust -- fit, frame, mend, (make) perfect(-ly join together), prepare, restore. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G739) artios
From  (G2675) katartizo; thorough equipment (subjectively) -- perfection. see GREEK  (G2675) katartizo
From  (G2675) katartizo; complete furnishing (objectively) -- perfecting. see GREEK  (G2675) katartizo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4579) seio; to sway downward, i.e. Make a signal -- beckon. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4579) seio
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4626) skapto; to undermine, i.e. (by implication) destroy -- dig down, ruin. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4626) skapto

From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G4632) skeuos; to prepare thoroughly (properly, by external equipment; whereas  (G2090) hetoimazo refers rather to internal fitness); by implication, to construct, create -- build, make, ordain, prepare. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4632) skeuos see GREEK  (G2090) hetoimazo

column7: to pitch one\'s tent, encamp, dwell
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G4637) skenoo; to camp down, i.e. Haunt; figuratively, to remain -- lodge, rest. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4637) skenoo
From  (G2681) kataskenoo; an encamping, i.e. (figuratively) a perch -- nest. see GREEK  (G2681) kataskenoo
From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G4639) skia; to overshade, i.e. Cover -- shadow. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4639) skia
From  (G2685) kataskopos; to be a sentinel, i.e. To inspect insidiously -- spy out. see GREEK  (G2685) kataskopos
From  (G2596) kata (intensive) and  (G4649) skopos (in the sense of a watcher); a reconnoiterer -- spy. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4649) skopos
Middle voice from  (G2596) kata and  (G4679) sophizo; to be crafty against, i.e. Circumvent -- deal subtilly with. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4679) sophizo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4724) stello; to put down, i.e. Quell -- appease, quiet. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4724) stello
From  (G2525) kathistemi; properly, a position or condition, i.e. (subjectively) demeanor -- behaviour. see GREEK  (G2525) kathistemi
From  (G2687) katastello; a deposit, i.e. (specially) costume -- apparel. see GREEK  (G2687) katastello
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4762) strepho; to turn upside down, i.e. Upset -- overthrow. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4762) strepho

column8: to be ruled by a physical desire
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G4763) streniao; to become voluptuous against -- begin to wax wanton against. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4763) streniao
From  (G2690) katastrepho; an overturn ("catastrophe"), i.e. Demolition; figuratively, apostasy -- overthrow, subverting. see GREEK  (G2690) katastrepho
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4766) stronnumi; to strew down, i.e. (by implication) to prostrate (slay) -- overthrow. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4766) stronnumi
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4951) suro; to drag down, i.e. Arrest judicially -- hale. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4951) suro
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4969) sphazo; to kill down, i.e. Slaughter -- slay. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4969) sphazo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G4972) sphragizo; to seal closely -- seal. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G4972) sphragizo
From  (G2722) katecho; a holding down, i.e. Occupancy -- possession. see GREEK  (G2722) katecho
From  (G2596) kata and  (G5087) tithemi; to place down, i.e. Deposit (literally or figuratively) -- do, lay, shew. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
From a compound of  (G2596) kata and temno (to cut); a cutting down (off), i.e. Mutilation (ironically) -- concision. Compare  (G609) apokopto. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G609) apokopto

column7: to strike down with an arrow
column9: From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G5115) toxon; to shoot down with an arrow or other missile -- thrust through. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5115) toxon
From  (G2596) kata and  (G5143) trecho; to run down, i.e. Hasten from a tower -- run down. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5143) trecho

From  (G2596) kata and  (G5342) phero (including its alternate); to bear down, i.e. (figuratively) overcome (with drowsiness); specially, to cast a vote -- fall, give, sink down. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5342) phero
From  (G2596) kata and  (G5343) pheugo; to flee down (away) -- flee. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5343) pheugo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G5351) phtheiro; to spoil entirely, i.e. (literally) to destroy; or (figuratively) to deprave; --corrupt, utterly perish. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5351) phtheiro
From  (G2596) kata and  (G5368) phileo; to kiss earnestly -- kiss.
From  (G2596) kata and  (G5426) phroneo; to think against, i.e. Disesteem -- despise. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5426) phroneo
From  (G2706) kataphroneo; a contemner -- despiser. see GREEK  (G2706) kataphroneo
From  (G2596) kata and cheo (to pour); to pour down (out) -- pour. see GREEK  (G2596) kata
From  (G2596) kata and chthon (the ground); subterranean, i.e. Infernal (belonging to the world of departed spirits) -- under the earth. see GREEK  (G2596) kata
From  (G2596) kata and  (G5530) chraomai; to overuse, i.e. Misuse -- abuse. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5530) chraomai
From  (G2596) kata and  (G5594) psucho; to cool down (off), i.e. Refresh -- cool. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5594) psucho
From  (G2596) kata (intensively) and  (G1497) eidolon; utterly idolatrous -- wholly given to idolatry. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1497) eidolon
From  (G2596) kata and  (G1725) enanti; directly opposite -- before, over against. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1725) enanti

column8: before, in the presence of, in the sight of.
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G1799) enopion; directly in front of -- before (the presence of), in the sight of. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1799) enopion
From  (G2596) kata and  (G1850) exousiazo; to have (wield) full privilege over -- exercise authority. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1850) exousiazo

From  (G2596) kata and  (G2038) ergazomai; to work fully, i.e. Accomplish; by implication, to finish, fashion -- cause, to (deed), perform, work (out). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2038) ergazomai

From  (G2596) kata and  (G2064) erchomai (including its alternate); to come (or go) down (literally or figuratively) -- come (down), depart, descend, go down, land. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2064) erchomai
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2068) esthio (including its alternate); to eat down, i.e. Devour (literally or figuratively) -- devour. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2068) esthio
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2116) euthuno; to straighten fully, i.e. (figuratively) direct -- guide, direct. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2116) euthuno
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2186) ephistemi; to stand over against, i.e. Rush upon (assault) -- make insurrection against. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2186) ephistemi

From  (G2596) kata and  (G2192) echo; to hold down (fast), in various applications (literally or figuratively) -- have, hold (fast), keep (in memory), let, X make toward, possess, retain, seize on, stay, take, withhold. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2192) echo
From  (G2725) kategoros; to be a plaintiff, i.e. To charge with some offence -- accuse, object. see GREEK  (G2725) kategoros
From  (G2725) kategoros; a complaint ("category"), i.e. Criminal charge -- accusation (X -ed). see GREEK  (G2725) kategoros
From  (G2596) kata and  (G58) agora; against one in the assembly, i.e. A complainant at law; specially, Satan -- accuser. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G58) agora

From a compound of  (G2596) kata and perhaps a derivative of the base of  (G5316) phaino (meaning downcast in look); demureness, i.e. (by implication) sadness -- heaviness. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G5316) phaino

column7: to teach by word of mouth
column9: From  (G2596) kata and  (G2279) echos; to sound down into the ears, i.e. (by implication) to indoctrinate ("catechize") or (genitive case) to apprise of -- inform, instruct, teach. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2279) echos
From  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G2447) ios; to rust down, i.e. Corrode -- canker. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2447) ios
From  (G2596) kata and  (G2480) ischuo; to overpower -- prevail (against). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2480) ischuo
From  (G2596) kata and  (G3611) oikeo; to house permanently, i.e. Reside (literally or figuratively) -- dwell(-er), inhabitant(-ter). see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3611) oikeo
From  (G2730) katoikeo; residence (properly, the act; but by implication, concretely, the mansion) -- dwelling. see GREEK  (G2730) katoikeo
From a derivative of  (G2730) katoikeo; a dwelling-place -- habitation. see GREEK  (G2730) katoikeo
Residence (properly, the condition; but by implication, the abode itself) -- habitation.

Middle voice from a compound of  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G3700) optanomai (compare  (G2072) esoptron); to mirror oneself, i.e. To see reflected (figuratively) -- behold as in a glass. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai see GREEK  (G2072) esoptron

From a compound of  (G2596) kata and a derivative of  (G3717) orthos (compare  (G1357) diorthosis); something made fully upright, i.e. (figuratively) rectification (specially, good public administration) -- very worthy deed. see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G3717) orthos see GREEK  (G1357) diorthosis
Also (compare) katotero (kat-o-ter'-o); (compare  (G2737) katoteros); adverb from  (G2596) kata; downwards -- beneath, bottom, down, under. see GREEK  (G2737) katoteros see GREEK  (G2596) kata
Comparative from  (G2736) kato; inferior (locally, of Hades) -- lower. see GREEK  (G2736) kato
From  (G2545) kaio; properly, a burn (concretely), but used (abstractly) of a glow -- heat. see GREEK  (G2545) kaio
From  (G2738) kauma; to burn -- scorch. see GREEK  (G2738) kauma
From  (G2545) kaio; burning (the act) -- be burned. see GREEK  (G2545) kaio
From  (G2740) kausis; to set on fire -- fervent heat. see GREEK  (G2740) kausis
From  (G2741) kausoo; a glare -- (burning) heat. see GREEK  (G2741) kausoo
From a derivative of  (G2545) kaio; to brand ("cauterize"), i.e. (by implication) to render unsensitive (figuratively) -- sear with a hot iron. see GREEK  (G2545) kaio
From some (obsolete) base akin to that of aucheo (to boast) and  (G2172) euchomai; to vaunt (in a good or a bad sense) -- (make) boast, glory, joy, rejoice. see GREEK  (G2172) euchomai
From  (G2744) kauchaomai; a boast (properly, the object; by implication, the act) in a good or a bad sense -- boasting, (whereof) to glory (of), glorying, rejoice(-ing). see GREEK  (G2744) kauchaomai
From  (G2744) kauchaomai; boasting (properly, the act; by implication, the object), in a good or a bad sense -- boasting, whereof I may glory, glorying, rejoicing. see GREEK  (G2744) kauchaomai
Probably from kegchros (millet); Cenchreae, a port of Corinth -- Cencrea.

column7: Kidron, a brook and wadi near Jer
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H6939) Qidrown); Cedron (i.e. Kidron), a brook near Jerusalem -- Cedron. see HEBREW  (H6939) Qidrown
Middle voice of a primary verb; to lie outstretched (literally or figuratively) -- be (appointed, laid up, made, set), lay, lie. Compare  (G5087) tithemi. see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
Of uncertain affinity; a swathe, i.e. Winding-sheet -- graveclothes.
A primary verb; to shear -- shear(-er).
From  (G2753) keleuo; a cry of incitement -- shout. see GREEK  (G2753) keleuo
From a primary kello (to urge on); "hail"; to incite by word, i.e. Order -- bid, (at, give) command(-ment).
From  (G2755) kenodoxos; empty glorying, i.e. Self-conceit -- vain-glory. see GREEK  (G2755) kenodoxos
From  (G2756) kenos and  (G1391) doxa; vainly glorifying, i.e. Self-conceited -- desirous of vain-glory. see GREEK  (G2756) kenos see GREEK  (G1391) doxa
Apparently a primary word; empty (literally or figuratively) -- empty, (in) vain.
From a presumed compound of  (G2756) kenos and  (G5456) phone; empty sounding, i.e. Fruitless discussion -- vain. see GREEK  (G2756) kenos see GREEK  (G5456) phone

column8: empty, make void, be in vain.
column9: From  (G2756) kenos; to make empty, i.e. (figuratively) to abase, neutralize, falsify -- make (of none effect, of no reputation, void), be in vain. see GREEK  (G2756) kenos
From kenteo (to prick); a point ("centre"), i.e. A sting (figuratively, poison) or goad (figuratively, divine impulse) -- prick, sting.
Of Latin origin; a centurion, i.e. Captain of one hundred soldiers -- centurion.
Adverb from  (G2756) kenos; vainly, i.e. To no purpose -- in vain. see GREEK  (G2756) kenos

Feminine of a presumed derivative of the base of  (G2768) keras; something horn-like, i.e. (specially) the apex of a Hebrew letter (figuratively, the least particle) -- tittle. see GREEK  (G2768) keras
